1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:33,680
I saw Chaiya sneaking into the room
behind the warehouse,

2
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:36,680
acting kind of strange.

3
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:38,160
How?

4
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:41,800
Maybe he's an undercover police captain
or something like that.

5
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:45,280
PREVIOUS EPISODE

6
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:47,840
Why didn't you tell me

7
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:50,920
that Mr. Sonrak has an interview
for a TV show in Bangkok?

8
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:55,240
I only know they contacted Mr. Sonrak
to record the show <i>Top Country Hits.</i>

9
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:57,280
I know you're tired, Puna.

10
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,680
I'm here to support you.

11
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:01,120
Thank you.

12
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:05,280
-Stop!
-Let go!

13
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:08,160
Let's go, Mr. Singha.

14
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:09,240
Go!

15
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:11,160
Hello. Is this the police?

16
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:13,240
Please send officers
to handle the situation.

17
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,240
Captain.

18
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:17,720
There's a clash happening.
We're not sure who's involved.

19
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:23,200
-Do you have any bullets left?
-None left.

20
00:03:31,040 --> 00:03:32,320
Grenade! Watch out!

21
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:47,880
We need to fall back
and regroup. Let's go!

22
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:50,960
He's running into the woods!

23
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:53,800
After him!

24
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,840
Go! Quick, move!

25
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,280
Get down!

26
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:16,600
Mr. Singha, we're here to help!

27
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:19,440
Where the hell have you been?
I was about to die!

28
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:27,240
We need to get out of here!

29
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:28,760
Lead the way. Go!

30
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:30,360
-Let's go, Boss!
-Go!

31
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:48,920
The gunfire's coming from over there.

32
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,960
Get ready, everyone.

33
00:04:51,520 --> 00:04:52,400
Go!

34
00:04:58,760 --> 00:05:01,000
What's up, Sergeant? Huh?

35
00:05:01,080 --> 00:05:02,280
Chart, the police are here.

36
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:05,200
Fall back! Fall back!

37
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:06,960
Got it. Let's go!

38
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,200
You think you can run?

39
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:16,280
Nuay, follow me.
The rest of you stay here.

40
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:20,440
Finish them off and follow me!

41
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:21,720
Got it!

42
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:25,080
Stop! Drop your weapons and surrender!

43
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,400
Hey, run!

44
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:30,920
Chase them down!

45
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,080
Yes, sir!

46
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:37,160
-Let's go, Sergeant!
-Let's go.

47
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:42,720
Let's go.

48
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:43,720
Stop!

49
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:45,640
Drop your weapons.

50
00:05:48,080 --> 00:05:49,440
I told you to drop your weapons!

51
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:04,920
You guys are all dead today.

52
00:06:05,840 --> 00:06:08,640
Singha, today's your last day.

53
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:10,680
Bring it on.

54
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:14,800
But if I make it out alive, your Boss Noo

55
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:17,200
is dead for sure.

56
00:06:17,280 --> 00:06:19,200
Keep dreaming.

57
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:21,680
Hey, pretty boy.

58
00:06:21,760 --> 00:06:23,760
This isn't your fight.

59
00:06:24,840 --> 00:06:25,960
But if you get involved…

60
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:27,040
Hey! Ugh!

61
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,720
Drop your gun!

62
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:33,720
If you don't, I'll shoot. Now!

63
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:52,000
Ugh!

64
00:06:58,360 --> 00:07:01,760
Oh, perfect evidence.

65
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:05,360
Gotcha.

66
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:09,320
Why is he so handsome?
Wait, why am I taking a selfie?

67
00:07:37,160 --> 00:07:38,880
Hey, the cops are coming!

68
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:41,000
Ugh!

69
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:51,400
-Which way should I go?
-This way, Boss!

70
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:53,720
-Let's go!
-Grab the guns too!

71
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:54,880
Protect the boss!

72
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:03,920
Sergeant.

73
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:06,000
How's it going?
Were you able to get the photos?

74
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:08,880
Yes, Captain. I got
clear shots of their faces.

75
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:11,240
Great job.

76
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:15,000
Hurry and send the evidence.
Then, follow Pleaw's crew.

77
00:08:15,960 --> 00:08:16,800
Got it, Captain.

78
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:20,960
-Hey, hold on!
-What?

79
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:32,080
They're all gone. Why are we still here?

80
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:36,559
We're here to collect evidence.
If you're free, please help with that.

81
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:46,600
They've all escaped.
All that's left are the bodies.

82
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:48,640
Then collect all the evidence in the area.

83
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:51,120
I want to know who those guys are,
who just fought.

84
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,440
Yes, Captain.

85
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:07,680
-Chart.
-The police got here too quickly today.

86
00:09:08,560 --> 00:09:11,200
Or do we have a mole among us?

87
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:14,800
And where's Chaiya?

88
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:28,680
Why are you just getting here?

89
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:32,760
Sorry, Mr. Singha.

90
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:35,960
There were so many cops around,
I barely escaped. That's why I'm late.

91
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:46,920
Go drive the car.

92
00:09:59,040 --> 00:10:01,440
Honestly, Chart, something
feels off about this guy.

93
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:03,840
Let it go for now.

94
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:06,440
Keep an eye on him from a distance.

95
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:54,880
Aha! Gotcha.

96
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:59,080
So this is where they've been hiding.

97
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:00,960
What's this?

98
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:04,560
You said there was
only one person with him.

99
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:06,360
Why couldn't you handle them?

100
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:08,880
But this guy is really skilled, Boss.

101
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:10,000
Who is he?

102
00:11:10,680 --> 00:11:12,240
His name is Chaiya.

103
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:16,080
I've met him before, and he's really good.

104
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:20,760
No matter how skilled,
he'll make a mistake one day.

105
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:23,480
Find a way to take him down.

106
00:11:24,080 --> 00:11:25,520
If you can't do it openly,

107
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:28,160
then do it quietly.

108
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:35,640
I'll never forget the pain from this.

109
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:40,840
Understood, Boss. I'll find a way.

110
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:58,040
Let's go.

111
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:01,840
Get in the van.

112
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:04,040
Yes.

113
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:11,520
Go check.

114
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:14,240
Alright, see you this evening.

115
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:17,680
Yeah, I hope so.

116
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:22,360
Puna, aren't you supposed
to be in the back seat?

117
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:23,520
When are you getting in the car?

118
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:24,840
We were about to get in!

119
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:26,680
You always talk back!

120
00:12:27,560 --> 00:12:30,200
Hey, why are you always shadowing me?

121
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:34,520
Hurry up, so others can get in!

122
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:39,920
You're wasting our time.

123
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:03,480
Mr. Sonrak, want to use
the bathroom? I'll take you.

124
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:05,000
Sure, let's go.

125
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,240
This way.

126
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:13,920
STUDIO SEVEN

127
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,720
Is the back seat comfortable, Puna?

128
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:17,920
How could it be comfortable?

129
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,480
She has to squeeze in
with bags of clothes,

130
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:22,800
and the van's bouncing and shaking.

131
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:24,000
If it were me,

132
00:13:24,080 --> 00:13:26,600
I wouldn't be able to sit at all.

133
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:29,920
Hey, Puna can handle it. She's good.

134
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:32,720
Don't use that word.
She's just used to it.

135
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:36,160
She's used to being like that.
As a lower-level employee,

136
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:37,400
she has to manage.

137
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:40,360
You can't compare her to Miss Maria.
Miss Maria's an artist.

138
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:44,880
<i>La la la</i>

139
00:13:48,680 --> 00:13:49,760
Keep mocking us!

140
00:13:50,680 --> 00:13:54,200
I think these guys want to get slapped!

141
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:55,680
Let it go, Teacher.

142
00:13:57,000 --> 00:14:00,280
Let them talk.
Just ignore them, and let them be.

143
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:03,320
-I'll let it go for now.
-Let's go.

144
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:12,800
<i>Take my heart for your consideration</i>

145
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:19,720
<i>Check it out and see</i>
<i>If my heart is new or old…</i>

146
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:21,800
What a beautiful song.

147
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:25,120
<i>Is it broken? Is there any damage…?</i>

148
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:28,920
It's Mr. Singha's song.
Mr. Sonrak had it sung again.

149
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:31,600
You know too much.

150
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:35,000
Of course I do. I'm his assistant.

151
00:14:35,880 --> 00:14:38,200
I know everything about Mr. Sonrak.

152
00:14:40,560 --> 00:14:43,720
You know everything about others,
but do you know yourself?

153
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:45,080
Of course I do.

154
00:14:46,120 --> 00:14:48,680
I know that I'm single right now,
with no girlfriend.

155
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:53,240
I'm looking for a serious relationship.

156
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:54,360
I've already found someone.

157
00:14:55,920 --> 00:14:57,080
It's the person next to me.

158
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:04,000
What does that mean?

159
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:06,640
See?

160
00:15:07,720 --> 00:15:11,160
I know my heart, unlike you.

161
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:12,440
You haven't been yourself.

162
00:15:13,800 --> 00:15:15,120
People are messing with your head.

163
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:17,560
Who are you talking about?

164
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:21,560
I'm not talking about anyone.
I'm just saying,

165
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:24,160
I want you to be yourself.

166
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:27,760
I feel like lately,
you've been getting messed with.

167
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:29,480
What am I being messed around with?

168
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:31,240
Competing and outdoing others.

169
00:15:32,920 --> 00:15:34,240
Let me ask you honestly.

170
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:38,600
If you win, are you truly happy

171
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:41,400
with a victory that comes
from hurting others?

172
00:15:43,080 --> 00:15:45,720
<i>If you still see</i>

173
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:48,720
<i>The value in my goodness</i>

174
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:51,640
<i>I'm ready to give my life</i>

175
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:56,960
<i>If you consider it…</i>

176
00:15:57,040 --> 00:15:58,440
Miss Maria.

177
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:01,600
STUDIO SEVEN

178
00:16:01,680 --> 00:16:05,040
Just now, what did
that assistant guy say to you?

179
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:08,160
Nothing, really.

180
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:12,000
That's good. Don't get too close to him.
You might soften up.

181
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:15,720
Right now, your focus
should only be on Mr. Sonrak.

182
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:17,320
Don't look at any other men.

183
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:19,960
See Mr. Sonrak?

184
00:16:20,040 --> 00:16:21,760
Keep your eyes on him, just on him.

185
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:24,200
That's the one. Over there.

186
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:27,200
That's the diamond.
Don't waste your time on the pebbles.

187
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:30,320
<i>Please, have mercy</i>

188
00:16:30,880 --> 00:16:34,320
-<i>Take the time to consider my heart…</i>
-Dazzling diamond!

189
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:37,040
So handsome!

190
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:40,520
<i>I offer you my heart</i>

191
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:43,960
<i>Waiting for your answer</i>

192
00:16:44,040 --> 00:16:47,400
<i>I'm ready for you to test it</i>

193
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:51,480
<i>Inside the chamber of my heart</i>

194
00:16:51,560 --> 00:16:53,280
MARIA

195
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:56,680
I heard a rumor that Village Head Prueng

196
00:16:56,760 --> 00:16:58,440
asked for Maria
to release her single first.

197
00:16:58,520 --> 00:17:00,160
I believe it's true.

198
00:17:00,760 --> 00:17:02,200
What do you think, Puna?

199
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:04,119
It doesn't matter.

200
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:08,160
Anyway, Maria is already a singer.

201
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:10,040
But if the village head
didn't play tricks,

202
00:17:10,119 --> 00:17:12,440
you would have already become
a singer by now.

203
00:17:12,520 --> 00:17:15,119
Who knows, the one filming the show today

204
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:18,760
might have been Puna Darathong,
not Maria.

205
00:17:29,320 --> 00:17:31,200
Puna.

206
00:17:33,760 --> 00:17:36,240
I'm sorry for what I said.

207
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:39,560
I didn't mean it.

208
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:44,240
I shouldn't have said that.

209
00:17:44,320 --> 00:17:48,000
You don't have to apologize.
You didn't do anything wrong.

210
00:17:50,640 --> 00:17:53,760
Everything you said is the truth.

211
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:57,200
I just have to accept it.

212
00:18:01,760 --> 00:18:05,760
But just wait.
If one day I can't take it anymore,

213
00:18:05,840 --> 00:18:07,280
you'll see what happens.

214
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:17,360
Oh, Maria!

215
00:18:17,440 --> 00:18:18,880
Hello, Teacher.

216
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:20,240
Are you all set?

217
00:18:20,320 --> 00:18:22,760
-Come on. Let me help you.
-Uh, no.

218
00:18:22,840 --> 00:18:24,480
It's fine. Don't be shy.

219
00:18:24,560 --> 00:18:27,440
Hurry, let's go.
I'll get your outfit ready.

220
00:18:27,520 --> 00:18:29,400
-Well…
-Okay, come here.

221
00:18:29,480 --> 00:18:31,720
Teacher, sorry for being late.

222
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:34,600
-Uh, okay.
-You look beautiful.

223
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:36,320
-Well, thank you.
-Really beautiful.

224
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:38,360
Thank you, but I'm…

225
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:39,880
-Just a little more.
-Alright.

226
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:41,480
Here.

227
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:43,400
-Huh?
-We're here. Oh no!

228
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:45,960
Excuse me. Hold on for a second.

229
00:18:46,040 --> 00:18:48,640
I think there's been a misunderstanding.

230
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:50,600
This isn't Miss Maria.

231
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:53,400
The real Miss Maria is right here.

232
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:55,680
This is Puna.

233
00:18:56,280 --> 00:18:58,600
Yes! She's just an employee.

234
00:18:58,680 --> 00:19:01,040
She prepares the clothes, irons them,

235
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:03,280
helps put them on, and serves the artists.

236
00:19:03,360 --> 00:19:06,160
But Puna won the singing competition

237
00:19:06,240 --> 00:19:08,400
and got first place, while Maria

238
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:10,320
only got second.

239
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:12,920
Don't forget to mention this,
so people know.

240
00:19:14,120 --> 00:19:15,480
Hey!

241
00:19:15,560 --> 00:19:19,280
Are you really a music teacher?
You have such a loose mouth.

242
00:19:19,360 --> 00:19:22,120
How can you reveal company secrets
in front of everyone?

243
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:24,400
What secret? Everyone knows about this.

244
00:19:24,480 --> 00:19:26,120
If you don't believe me,
check out the Facebook page

245
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:28,040
of Darathong Music. But wait,

246
00:19:29,120 --> 00:19:30,720
you won't find it now.

247
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:32,960
Because Maria's dad…

248
00:19:34,760 --> 00:19:38,840
Oops, the label
deleted the results already.

249
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:43,280
Miss Maria, don't let him get to you.

250
00:19:43,360 --> 00:19:46,160
He's exposing you.

251
00:19:46,240 --> 00:19:47,360
-Joey!
-Ouch!

252
00:19:48,320 --> 00:19:49,480
I won't say anything.

253
00:19:50,280 --> 00:19:54,400
But anyway, right now,
Miss Maria is the artist.

254
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:57,520
And Puna is just a staff.

255
00:19:58,360 --> 00:20:00,480
Everyone has a role,
so they should stick to it.

256
00:20:00,560 --> 00:20:02,720
Isn't that right?

257
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:06,480
Yeah, Puna's job
is to prepares the clothes.

258
00:20:06,560 --> 00:20:09,600
Go help put the clothes on
and iron them. Got it?

259
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:10,960
Hey, stylist.

260
00:20:11,040 --> 00:20:13,680
Miss Maria will change,
then come back for makeup and hair.

261
00:20:13,760 --> 00:20:15,680
As for you,

262
00:20:15,760 --> 00:20:17,600
go help her get dressed.

263
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:21,120
Hurry up, Puna. Come on!

264
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:24,040
Hurry up! You weren't hired
to stand around.

265
00:20:25,640 --> 00:20:28,480
Tsk! You don't even know your place!

266
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:39,840
Ouch, that hurts!

267
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:41,760
Just stay still.

268
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:46,000
Are you trying to mess with me?

269
00:20:46,080 --> 00:20:49,080
Why would I mess with you?
Turn around quickly.

270
00:21:02,640 --> 00:21:07,400
Oh, you had to follow Puna
all the way here.

271
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:11,240
Probably worried that she might
get hurt by Miss Maria.

272
00:21:12,960 --> 00:21:13,840
You never know.

273
00:21:24,680 --> 00:21:27,040
Joey, do you see that?

274
00:21:27,120 --> 00:21:29,200
If not, I wouldn't be like this.

275
00:21:30,680 --> 00:21:33,120
All this food looks so good!

276
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:36,360
I want to sneak some and take it home.
Do you have a bag?

277
00:21:36,440 --> 00:21:38,760
This set is amazing. So much food to eat!

278
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:41,800
Next time, I'll bring a bag
and take some home.

279
00:21:43,360 --> 00:21:44,600
Wow.

280
00:21:45,760 --> 00:21:49,000
Are you bringing a big bag to put it in?
Are you planning to sell it?

281
00:21:49,080 --> 00:21:52,600
Your idea is good!
Should I sell them after taking them?

282
00:21:52,680 --> 00:21:53,840
-No!
-What?

283
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:56,080
That's rude! I should sell them too.

284
00:21:57,720 --> 00:21:59,040
Hurry up. Let's go!

285
00:22:01,960 --> 00:22:05,160
A bunch of gluttons stealing food!

286
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:10,760
If you're being oppressed,
you need to stay even calmer.

287
00:22:10,840 --> 00:22:12,960
Don't do anything reckless.

288
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:19,720
-Where are my heels?
-They're right there.

289
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:26,360
Pick them up and put them on for me.

290
00:22:27,920 --> 00:22:32,000
Do it yourself.
Can't you see I'm busy working?

291
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:37,000
But I'm the artist.

292
00:22:37,080 --> 00:22:39,840
And you're just a clothes ironer.

293
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:44,800
When you're done,
come put my shoes on for me.

294
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:47,880
Or I'll tell Mr. Singha
you're slacking off.

295
00:22:59,760 --> 00:23:00,680
Wait.

296
00:23:02,280 --> 00:23:05,200
Clean them first, then put them on for me.

297
00:23:18,920 --> 00:23:21,400
You better know your place, Puna.

298
00:23:22,280 --> 00:23:26,240
Your fate is probably
just to be an employee.

299
00:23:28,600 --> 00:23:32,680
You should remember
who I am and who you are.

300
00:23:34,360 --> 00:23:38,280
In the future, if I become
Mr. Sonrak's girlfriend,

301
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:42,320
I'd probably end up
being the president's wife.

302
00:23:43,640 --> 00:23:45,120
At that point, I might show some mercy

303
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:49,880
and promote you
to a coffee-making employee.

304
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:57,120
Are you done yet?

305
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:59,600
When you're finished, put them on for me.

306
00:24:26,880 --> 00:24:27,760
I can't take it anymore!

307
00:24:28,360 --> 00:24:30,280
Come here!

308
00:24:30,360 --> 00:24:33,720
Hey, you watch
too many moral dramas, don't you?

309
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:35,280
What are you going to do to me?

310
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:42,320
Do you want to know what happens
to the villains in those dramas?

311
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:44,040
How do you think their story ends?

312
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:46,640
No, I don't want to know.

313
00:24:47,600 --> 00:24:51,080
If you don't want to know, that's fine.
I'll make you find out.

314
00:24:53,120 --> 00:24:55,200
Stay away! Don't!

315
00:24:55,280 --> 00:24:56,600
What are you going to do?

316
00:24:56,680 --> 00:24:58,360
Why? Are you scared?

317
00:24:58,960 --> 00:25:01,960
Stay away! Hey, don't come closer!

318
00:25:02,040 --> 00:25:05,080
-Come here!
-No! What are you going to do to me?

319
00:25:05,160 --> 00:25:06,680
Take it off!

320
00:25:08,280 --> 00:25:11,240
-Take it off!
-Puna, let me go!

321
00:25:12,280 --> 00:25:14,160
Hey, Puna!

322
00:25:14,240 --> 00:25:16,080
Let me go right now!

323
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:19,920
Puna! You can't
keep me locked up like this!

324
00:25:20,480 --> 00:25:22,400
Scream all you want. No one will hear.

325
00:25:24,280 --> 00:25:27,880
Are you done? It's time for standby now.

326
00:25:31,040 --> 00:25:32,560
You look amazing!

327
00:25:34,320 --> 00:25:35,240
Thank you so much.

328
00:25:35,320 --> 00:25:36,600
Let's go.

329
00:25:44,320 --> 00:25:46,800
Puna! Let me go!

330
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:51,640
<i>Who owns this famous music label?</i>
<i>They say the boss</i>

331
00:25:51,720 --> 00:25:54,640
<i>Is good-looking</i>

332
00:25:54,720 --> 00:25:57,600
<i>The singers of this label are all handsome</i>

333
00:25:57,680 --> 00:26:00,600
<i>And famous, at the top level</i>

334
00:26:00,680 --> 00:26:04,920
<i>I want to be famous, I want to try</i>
<i>I want to be one of the artists</i>

335
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:07,480
<i>At this label</i>

336
00:26:07,560 --> 00:26:10,520
<i>I want to be famous</i>
<i>Can't stand it anymore</i>

337
00:26:10,600 --> 00:26:13,800
<i>I want people</i>
<i>To scream for me at the stage</i>

338
00:26:13,880 --> 00:26:16,320
<i>Please accept me as an artist</i>

339
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:21,200
<i>I promise I'll do well</i>

340
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:23,160
<i>No cheating, no running away</i>

341
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:27,280
<i>I'll sign a contract for years</i>
<i>If you want me to</i>

342
00:26:27,360 --> 00:26:31,360
<i>I want to be famous, like a star</i>
<i>I want everyone</i>

343
00:26:31,440 --> 00:26:33,680
<i>To cheer together</i>

344
00:26:33,760 --> 00:26:36,800
<i>I'm serious about being famous</i>

345
00:26:36,880 --> 00:26:41,160
<i>Let the music label fulfill my dream</i>
<i>I want to be famous…</i>

346
00:26:49,560 --> 00:26:50,920
Puna!

347
00:26:52,640 --> 00:26:53,800
Puna!

348
00:26:56,760 --> 00:26:59,720
What's wrong with you?
Why are you zoning out?

349
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:03,120
Are you done yet? I'm in a hurry!

350
00:27:04,040 --> 00:27:05,280
Almost done.

351
00:27:13,680 --> 00:27:15,520
Took forever.
Where were you lost in thought?

352
00:27:25,320 --> 00:27:27,200
Anyway, in the future,

353
00:27:27,280 --> 00:27:30,840
if I become the wife of Mr. Sonrak,
the company president,

354
00:27:30,920 --> 00:27:33,800
I'll give you the position
of shoe assistant.

355
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:37,240
Thank you for your kindness.

356
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:40,360
Miss Maria! Oh!

357
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:42,080
Are you wearing this outfit?

358
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:45,240
Yes, is there a problem?

359
00:27:45,320 --> 00:27:48,280
The producer wants you
to wear a different outfit.

360
00:27:48,360 --> 00:27:51,360
The one you wore
for the promotional poster shoot.

361
00:27:51,440 --> 00:27:54,760
The team already informed
Miss Sophie about it.

362
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:57,000
Sophie!

363
00:27:57,720 --> 00:27:59,000
Sophie!

364
00:27:59,080 --> 00:28:00,720
Yes, Miss Maria. What's wrong?

365
00:28:01,640 --> 00:28:04,680
The team said to bring the poster outfit.
Why didn't you tell me?

366
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:06,160
Oh!

367
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:08,920
-When was this mentioned?
-It was mentioned.

368
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:11,280
We even discussed through texts.
Do you want to see it?

369
00:28:12,360 --> 00:28:13,240
Puna!

370
00:28:13,320 --> 00:28:15,240
Why didn't you bring it?

371
00:28:15,320 --> 00:28:17,720
Well, no one told me.

372
00:28:17,800 --> 00:28:19,320
I told you. I remember.

373
00:28:19,400 --> 00:28:21,360
When did you tell her? How do I not know?

374
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:23,800
-She told you when you weren't there.
-Yeah!

375
00:28:23,880 --> 00:28:26,400
That's not true. You didn't tell me.

376
00:28:26,480 --> 00:28:27,800
Can we stop arguing?

377
00:28:27,880 --> 00:28:30,640
Let's focus on solving the problem.

378
00:28:30,720 --> 00:28:32,120
Can we wear another outfit?

379
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:33,400
No.

380
00:28:33,480 --> 00:28:36,880
It doesn't fit the theme of the show.
How about this?

381
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:39,160
Can you go get it?

382
00:28:39,240 --> 00:28:41,520
-Go get it?
-Yes.

383
00:28:43,200 --> 00:28:44,480
Yes!

384
00:28:44,560 --> 00:28:46,400
You go get it. Quickly!

385
00:28:47,360 --> 00:28:48,440
Hurry up!

386
00:28:48,520 --> 00:28:52,760
I'll go. Puna, tell me
where you keep the outfit.

387
00:28:54,040 --> 00:28:58,640
It's okay. The outfit is in the box.
You won't find it. I'll go get it.

388
00:28:58,720 --> 00:29:01,800
We'll move forward
with another shoot in the meantime.

389
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:04,280
But please hurry up.

390
00:29:04,360 --> 00:29:05,840
-Okay.
-Alright.

391
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:07,280
I'll go now.

392
00:29:07,360 --> 00:29:08,800
Hurry up. Go!

393
00:29:09,840 --> 00:29:10,880
Go!

394
00:29:11,600 --> 00:29:13,480
This is how you work?

395
00:29:13,560 --> 00:29:16,680
STUDIO SEVEN

396
00:29:16,760 --> 00:29:18,000
-Chang.
-What?

397
00:29:18,080 --> 00:29:20,680
I need to go back to the company
to pick up an outfit.

398
00:29:20,760 --> 00:29:22,680
Can you give me a ride?

399
00:29:22,760 --> 00:29:24,080
How do you all work like this?

400
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:26,760
Always causing trouble for others.

401
00:29:26,840 --> 00:29:28,680
This isn't Puna's fault.

402
00:29:28,760 --> 00:29:30,680
We only just found out

403
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:32,960
they need the poster outfit.

404
00:29:33,040 --> 00:29:34,400
Please help her out.

405
00:29:34,480 --> 00:29:35,520
I can't.

406
00:29:35,600 --> 00:29:38,160
I need to stay here
and look after Mr. Sonrak.

407
00:29:38,760 --> 00:29:41,200
-I can't leave.
-Then I'll go.

408
00:29:45,240 --> 00:29:47,800
Thanks. I'll go ahead now, Teacher.

409
00:29:49,280 --> 00:29:50,800
Hurry up and come back quickly.

410
00:29:51,800 --> 00:29:53,640
If you're late,

411
00:29:54,480 --> 00:29:55,760
I'll report you to Mr. Sonrak.

412
00:29:56,360 --> 00:29:57,200
Please go ahead.

413
00:30:03,400 --> 00:30:05,400
Hey, do it right! Come here.

414
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:07,360
Take it properly! Good!

415
00:30:14,040 --> 00:30:16,840
<i>Who owns this famous music label?</i>

416
00:30:16,920 --> 00:30:20,960
<i>They say the boss is good looking</i>

417
00:30:21,040 --> 00:30:23,240
<i>The singers of this label…</i>

418
00:30:23,320 --> 00:30:25,520
Yes, I got it.

419
00:30:25,600 --> 00:30:26,760
Understood.

420
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:28,840
Thank you!

421
00:30:30,200 --> 00:30:31,040
Director.

422
00:30:31,120 --> 00:30:32,760
Maria forgot

423
00:30:32,840 --> 00:30:34,800
to bring the poster outfit.

424
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:37,680
Can we start
with the interview tape instead?

425
00:30:38,880 --> 00:30:39,720
Sure.

426
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:44,680
Hey, Praewa, you're here just in time.
I need a favor.

427
00:30:45,560 --> 00:30:46,440
What is it?

428
00:30:46,520 --> 00:30:49,920
Can you host the show for me?

429
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:52,640
You want me to interview for the show?

430
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:55,080
Yeah. Please help me out.

431
00:30:55,160 --> 00:30:56,400
Sure, I'll do it.

432
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:02,600
DARATHONG MUSIC

433
00:31:02,680 --> 00:31:03,720
Chaiya.

434
00:31:04,480 --> 00:31:05,480
Yes, Ice?

435
00:31:05,560 --> 00:31:07,760
Mr. Singha wants to see you in his office.

436
00:31:12,920 --> 00:31:14,160
Come in.

437
00:31:17,960 --> 00:31:19,720
What's going on, Mr. Singha?

438
00:31:19,800 --> 00:31:21,120
I have a job for you.

439
00:31:25,120 --> 00:31:26,000
What kind of job?

440
00:31:26,080 --> 00:31:27,640
Get revenge on Boss Noo.

441
00:31:37,280 --> 00:31:39,080
We know where he is now.

442
00:31:40,040 --> 00:31:42,480
I want you to deal with him today.

443
00:31:43,480 --> 00:31:46,240
But we just clashed with him.

444
00:31:46,320 --> 00:31:49,080
Exactly! Don't give him
any chance to regroup.

445
00:31:49,160 --> 00:31:50,280
You know,

446
00:31:51,400 --> 00:31:53,200
I almost died because of him today.

447
00:31:53,280 --> 00:31:54,720
Blow his head off, so he won't forget it.

448
00:31:56,240 --> 00:31:58,480
You can do that, right, Chaiya?

449
00:32:00,600 --> 00:32:01,440
But…

450
00:32:02,680 --> 00:32:03,800
I've never killed anyone.

451
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:07,200
Hey! Are you disobeying my orders?

452
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:32,560
Did Mr. Singha scold you?
You look really stressed.

453
00:32:34,040 --> 00:32:34,880
Just a little bit.

454
00:32:35,640 --> 00:32:37,320
Don't worry too much.

455
00:32:37,400 --> 00:32:39,920
Being his subordinate
means you have to be patient.

456
00:32:41,960 --> 00:32:44,680
Okay, I'll be patient, just like you said.

457
00:32:45,280 --> 00:32:48,880
Ice, with looks like yours,
don't you ever get scared being here?

458
00:32:48,960 --> 00:32:51,440
I can handle myself just fine.

459
00:32:56,920 --> 00:33:00,160
I'm going to grab something to eat.
I haven't eaten all day.

460
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:01,800
Sure, take your time.

461
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:13,160
Yes, Captain?

462
00:33:13,840 --> 00:33:17,600
Hey, who am I? This is Sergeant Au.

463
00:33:17,680 --> 00:33:19,560
I've found their hideout.

464
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:23,000
I also got a photo. How's that?

465
00:33:23,080 --> 00:33:24,200
Great job, Sergeant Au.

466
00:33:24,280 --> 00:33:26,720
Captain, what should I do next?

467
00:33:28,280 --> 00:33:30,680
Quickly send the photo you took
to Captain Tom.

468
00:33:30,760 --> 00:33:33,240
So, you want him to handle it?

469
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:36,800
Well…

470
00:33:36,880 --> 00:33:39,200
I have something important today
that requires his help.

471
00:33:40,080 --> 00:33:41,400
Find a way to send it for me.

472
00:33:41,480 --> 00:33:44,920
How should I send it?
Sergeant Yot isn't here anymore.

473
00:33:48,720 --> 00:33:52,680
Uncle Sergeant said Corporal Chom
is trustworthy.

474
00:33:53,200 --> 00:33:54,280
Just send it to him.

475
00:33:54,360 --> 00:33:57,000
Okay, I'll take care of it.

476
00:34:04,240 --> 00:34:05,240
What are you looking at?

477
00:34:06,560 --> 00:34:08,600
A picture of Boss Noo and Pleaw.

478
00:34:08,679 --> 00:34:10,719
Looks like someone found his hideout,

479
00:34:10,800 --> 00:34:12,199
so they sent the photo to the police.

480
00:34:12,280 --> 00:34:13,679
Prepare the forces.

481
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:14,639
Yes, sir.

482
00:34:14,719 --> 00:34:16,239
We're going in to capture them.

483
00:34:16,320 --> 00:34:18,520
Alright, go get the team ready.

484
00:34:18,600 --> 00:34:19,560
Understood.

485
00:34:31,800 --> 00:34:35,560
Chaiya, where have you been?
I've been looking for you forever.

486
00:34:35,639 --> 00:34:38,239
What's up? Just went to eat.

487
00:34:38,320 --> 00:34:40,400
You better go take care of Boss Noo.

488
00:34:40,920 --> 00:34:43,760
I've got a driver waiting for you
outside the building.

489
00:34:43,840 --> 00:34:45,159
Are you coming along?

490
00:34:45,239 --> 00:34:47,639
Whether I go or not
has nothing to do with you.

491
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:53,480
Hurry up, unless you want me
to roll out the red carpet.

492
00:34:55,120 --> 00:34:56,239
Go!

493
00:35:07,680 --> 00:35:09,280
-Chit.
-Yes?

494
00:35:09,360 --> 00:35:11,120
Come with me and handle the job.

495
00:35:11,200 --> 00:35:12,240
Got it.

496
00:35:13,120 --> 00:35:14,880
If Chaiya messes around,

497
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:18,040
kill him along with Boss Noo.

498
00:35:24,840 --> 00:35:27,560
Someone just texted
these photos to me, Captain.

499
00:35:28,560 --> 00:35:31,760
The superintendent saw it
and ordered you to capture them.

500
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:35,360
Captain.

501
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:38,000
Is there a problem
with the superintendent's orders?

502
00:35:38,080 --> 00:35:39,400
What problem could there be?

503
00:35:39,480 --> 00:35:41,240
Good, no problem.

504
00:35:41,320 --> 00:35:43,280
Make sure to capture them.

505
00:35:43,360 --> 00:35:45,240
Now, get going.

506
00:35:46,560 --> 00:35:47,600
Let's go.

507
00:36:01,240 --> 00:36:02,520
Wait, Manat.

508
00:36:05,400 --> 00:36:07,560
If we go the usual way,
we'll never make it in time.

509
00:36:08,800 --> 00:36:09,800
Do you know a shortcut?

510
00:36:09,880 --> 00:36:12,280
Let's turn right ahead. It's a shortcut.

511
00:36:13,040 --> 00:36:13,960
Alright.

512
00:36:29,600 --> 00:36:31,640
There they are, over there.

513
00:36:38,200 --> 00:36:40,440
If we charge in now, we won't make it.

514
00:36:41,600 --> 00:36:44,120
Come on. Just find the right moment!

515
00:36:52,080 --> 00:36:53,320
It's Chart calling.

516
00:36:56,680 --> 00:36:57,560
Yes?

517
00:36:57,640 --> 00:36:59,720
What are you hesitating for?

518
00:37:00,480 --> 00:37:01,760
Go in and shoot them.

519
00:37:01,840 --> 00:37:04,880
But Pleaw and his men are standing there.

520
00:37:04,960 --> 00:37:06,200
What are you afraid of?

521
00:37:06,280 --> 00:37:07,760
Well…

522
00:37:09,240 --> 00:37:10,640
I'm still a rookie, Chart.

523
00:37:12,280 --> 00:37:13,320
Chit.

524
00:37:17,280 --> 00:37:19,000
If you don't shoot,

525
00:37:19,960 --> 00:37:21,440
I'll order him to shoot you.

526
00:37:29,440 --> 00:37:32,280
Well, calm down, Chart.

527
00:37:32,880 --> 00:37:35,920
Give me a moment.
I need to collect myself.

528
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:37,920
Just a second, okay?

529
00:37:55,600 --> 00:37:57,200
When will the police arrive?

530
00:38:03,840 --> 00:38:06,240
This is it. Everyone, get ready!

531
00:38:07,040 --> 00:38:07,960
Go!

532
00:38:08,960 --> 00:38:10,880
Boss, the police are raiding.

533
00:38:12,040 --> 00:38:13,120
How did they find out?

534
00:38:13,200 --> 00:38:14,360
Go out and block them.

535
00:38:14,960 --> 00:38:16,840
Don't let them in. Go!

536
00:38:16,920 --> 00:38:17,920
Got it.

537
00:38:21,880 --> 00:38:23,440
We better hide, Boss.

538
00:38:24,720 --> 00:38:25,760
Let's go!

539
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:31,000
Hey, stop!

540
00:38:41,040 --> 00:38:43,040
You two go that way.

541
00:38:43,120 --> 00:38:44,760
And you, follow me!

542
00:38:46,560 --> 00:38:48,080
You two go that way!

543
00:38:48,720 --> 00:38:49,960
Let's go, quickly!

544
00:38:50,040 --> 00:38:51,320
Senior Sergeant, follow me!

545
00:38:56,120 --> 00:38:57,000
Watch out!

546
00:38:57,080 --> 00:38:58,200
Hey!

547
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:03,360
Puna, get out of here.

548
00:39:03,440 --> 00:39:04,360
I'll handle this.

549
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:19,240
Hey! Watch out!

550
00:39:27,920 --> 00:39:28,840
Run!

551
00:39:31,360 --> 00:39:32,400
Puna.

552
00:39:33,760 --> 00:39:37,040
Chaiya, hurry up and run! Daddy's coming!

553
00:39:41,720 --> 00:39:43,400
-Puna?
-Hurry up!

554
00:39:43,920 --> 00:39:45,040
Hey, Chaiya!

555
00:40:22,120 --> 00:40:23,600
What are you doing here?

556
00:40:24,840 --> 00:40:27,000
I came with Manat.
We were going back to get something.

557
00:40:27,720 --> 00:40:28,800
What happened, Chaiya?

558
00:40:29,600 --> 00:40:32,080
Boss Noo and his men
are being raided by the police.

559
00:40:32,160 --> 00:40:33,040
-Boss, get down!
-Hey!

560
00:40:33,640 --> 00:40:34,960
-Oh no!
-Get down!

561
00:40:49,080 --> 00:40:50,360
Let's go, Boss.

562
00:40:54,960 --> 00:40:56,360
Pleaw, help him up.

563
00:40:58,680 --> 00:40:59,520
Hey.

564
00:41:02,360 --> 00:41:04,080
That way, Boss.

565
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:05,040
Let's go.

566
00:41:10,680 --> 00:41:14,360
Chaiya, what's happening?
What's your issue with them?

567
00:41:15,400 --> 00:41:17,840
You don't need to know.
It's too dangerous.

568
00:41:24,520 --> 00:41:27,880
Stay hidden here. Don't go anywhere.
I'll be back.

569
00:41:36,040 --> 00:41:37,520
Chaiya!

570
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:41,920
Chart.

571
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:42,960
What are you doing here?

572
00:41:44,240 --> 00:41:46,440
I saw Boss Noo around here,

573
00:41:46,520 --> 00:41:47,800
so I was…

574
00:41:47,880 --> 00:41:49,000
Good.

575
00:41:49,880 --> 00:41:52,160
Kill Boss Noo
while he's escaping the police.

576
00:41:52,240 --> 00:41:53,440
That way, no one will know.

577
00:41:54,880 --> 00:41:56,480
I'll go corner him for you.

578
00:41:57,880 --> 00:42:00,320
Then you shoot him in the head,

579
00:42:00,400 --> 00:42:03,600
or I'll shoot you instead.

580
00:42:07,320 --> 00:42:08,280
Follow me.

581
00:42:35,040 --> 00:42:38,440
Now's the time. Take him out, Chaiya.

582
00:42:41,920 --> 00:42:43,200
Hold on.

583
00:42:45,040 --> 00:42:48,440
Are you going to shoot him,
or do you want me to shoot you?

584
00:42:52,160 --> 00:42:53,120
Hurry up!

585
00:43:00,560 --> 00:43:02,560
-This way, Boss.
-Let's go!

586
00:43:09,440 --> 00:43:11,400
Hey, the police are coming. We should run.

587
00:43:11,480 --> 00:43:12,600
Let's go.

588
00:43:19,160 --> 00:43:22,240
Stay here, Corporal. I'll check that way.

589
00:43:22,760 --> 00:43:23,960
-Yes.
-Okay.

590
00:43:24,960 --> 00:43:26,360
Who's there?

591
00:43:26,440 --> 00:43:28,560
Come out, or I'll shoot!

592
00:43:31,200 --> 00:43:32,200
Officer!

593
00:43:33,640 --> 00:43:35,120
What are you doing here?

594
00:43:35,840 --> 00:43:37,200
I'm running from the criminals.

595
00:43:37,280 --> 00:43:40,000
They ambushed me.
My van's broken. I can't go anywhere.

596
00:43:40,080 --> 00:43:41,440
Where's your van?

597
00:43:42,440 --> 00:43:43,720
Over there. I'll take you to it.

598
00:43:44,320 --> 00:43:45,240
Let's go.

599
00:43:52,600 --> 00:43:54,360
Stop, Boss Noo, if you don't want to die!

600
00:43:54,440 --> 00:43:55,520
A man like me

601
00:43:55,600 --> 00:43:57,840
doesn't die so easily
if I've done nothing wrong!

602
00:44:14,680 --> 00:44:16,440
Boss, let's get out of here.

603
00:44:17,640 --> 00:44:20,000
-Come on!
-Let's go!

604
00:44:21,200 --> 00:44:22,280
Ouch!

605
00:44:23,240 --> 00:44:24,200
Take cover!

606
00:44:25,880 --> 00:44:26,920
Ugh!

607
00:44:27,800 --> 00:44:29,000
Are you okay, Boss?

608
00:44:29,080 --> 00:44:30,720
-I'm fine!
-Go!

609
00:45:08,160 --> 00:45:09,440
This is what happened.

610
00:45:09,520 --> 00:45:12,480
I was driving along when they appeared
and started shooting at me.

611
00:45:12,560 --> 00:45:14,480
I had to swerve off the road

612
00:45:14,560 --> 00:45:17,280
and hit a tree, radiator busted.
I almost died.

613
00:45:17,880 --> 00:45:18,960
Where are you going?

614
00:45:19,040 --> 00:45:20,840
Back to get the clothes from the company.

615
00:45:22,600 --> 00:45:23,720
Open it up.

616
00:45:29,600 --> 00:45:31,720
The artists need costumes for the show.

617
00:45:33,800 --> 00:45:35,560
Not sure where my crew has gone.

618
00:45:36,720 --> 00:45:38,440
I need to call them.

619
00:45:39,160 --> 00:45:40,520
Alright, okay.

620
00:45:57,280 --> 00:45:59,120
Captain, how did it go?

621
00:45:59,200 --> 00:46:00,800
Boss Noo and Pleaw managed to escape.

622
00:46:00,880 --> 00:46:03,200
What a shame we couldn't catch them.

623
00:46:03,280 --> 00:46:06,320
Boss Noo got shot.
I think tracking him won't be too hard.

624
00:46:06,400 --> 00:46:09,000
Send someone
to the hospitals or other places.

625
00:46:09,080 --> 00:46:11,040
He might go get treated.

626
00:46:11,120 --> 00:46:13,000
-Yes, sir.
-Corporal Chom.

627
00:46:13,600 --> 00:46:15,920
I really want to know
who's your informant.

628
00:46:16,000 --> 00:46:18,400
How do they know
such detailed information?

629
00:46:18,480 --> 00:46:19,960
This person isn't my usual source.

630
00:46:20,040 --> 00:46:22,200
Somehow, they just sent
Boss Noo's location.

631
00:46:22,280 --> 00:46:24,520
I'll try to find out who it is.

632
00:46:24,600 --> 00:46:25,880
Good. Very good.

633
00:46:25,960 --> 00:46:26,800
Yes.

634
00:46:36,880 --> 00:46:37,840
Puna!

635
00:46:38,440 --> 00:46:40,680
Puna! Where are you?

636
00:46:43,120 --> 00:46:44,040
Puna!

637
00:46:44,560 --> 00:46:45,480
Chaiya.

638
00:46:47,360 --> 00:46:48,200
Puna's not here?

639
00:46:49,720 --> 00:46:50,720
She's not.

640
00:46:51,480 --> 00:46:54,720
-Maybe she already left?
-How? There aren't any taxis.

641
00:46:55,640 --> 00:46:58,520
The van we drove can't continue.

642
00:46:59,960 --> 00:47:01,040
I'll call Au to pick us up.

643
00:47:03,240 --> 00:47:06,000
Hello, Au? Where are you?
I'm here with Chaiya.

644
00:47:06,080 --> 00:47:08,160
Alright, you want to talk to Chaiya?

645
00:47:11,760 --> 00:47:14,640
Hey, Sergeant Au.
If the police hadn't arrived in time,

646
00:47:15,960 --> 00:47:17,240
I'd have been the shooter.

647
00:47:17,320 --> 00:47:20,240
Don't worry about the message
you sent to Corporal Chom.

648
00:47:21,280 --> 00:47:22,880
He won't be able to trace us.

649
00:47:23,920 --> 00:47:26,720
The number I'm using is encrypted by HQ,

650
00:47:26,800 --> 00:47:28,560
so it can't be traced back to us.

651
00:47:28,640 --> 00:47:31,680
Hurry and pick us up.
I'll send the location.

652
00:47:41,480 --> 00:47:42,360
Puna.

653
00:47:42,440 --> 00:47:44,080
Who exactly are you guys?

654
00:47:56,720 --> 00:47:58,240
Tell the people at home for me.

655
00:47:58,760 --> 00:47:59,840
Tell them what?

656
00:47:59,920 --> 00:48:02,080
NEXT EPISODE

657
00:48:09,440 --> 00:48:10,720
What are you two doing here?

658
00:48:13,760 --> 00:48:15,680
Hey, wait.

659
00:48:16,280 --> 00:48:19,000
-<i>Don't let anyone kiss this forehead</i>
-Hey.

660
00:48:19,080 --> 00:48:20,360
Is that Chaiya's voice?

661
00:48:20,440 --> 00:48:22,280
<i>Don't let anyone caress these cheeks</i>

662
00:48:22,360 --> 00:48:24,520
Yes, that's him singing.

663
00:51:24,360 --> 00:51:27,360
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
